<inglise> - promotion of pilot alternative development projects, conceived as a process by which the production of illicit drug crops is eventually both combatted and eliminated through appropriate rural development measures in the context of sustained national economic growth. </inglise>
<eesti> - edendada selliseid alternatiivse arengu katseprojekte, mille kaudu nii v&otilde;ideldakse ebaseaduslike uimastikultuuride viljelemise vastu kui ka l&otilde;petatakse nende viljelemine kohaste maapiirkondade arendamise meetmete abil p&uuml;siva siseriikliku majanduskasvu raames. </eesti>
<inglise> These projects shall comprise social and economic measures which take into account factors contributing to illicit production as well as measures which may facilitate improved use of commercial preferences. </inglise>
<eesti> Need projektid h&otilde;lmavad sotsiaalseid ja majanduslikke meetmeid, mille puhul v&otilde;etakse arvesse ebaseaduslikku tootmist soodustavaid tegureid, samuti meetmeid, mis v&otilde;ivad h&otilde;lbustada kaubandussoodustuste t&otilde;husamat kasutamist. </eesti>
<inglise> In this connection, it shall be systematically examined whether it is possible to make more use of other Community financial instruments (e.g. ALA) and the European Development Fund for alternative development projects, </inglise>
